=begin
      author: Fizzleworth, Ashraam
        name: fizzsac
        game: gemstone
        tags: sorcerer, sacrifice, shadow essence, combat
    requires: Lich > 5.14.2
     version: 0.6
        note: Written with assistance from Claude (Anthropic).

  This script was designed to help detect whether a target is ready for Sorcerer Sacrifice.

	If you have less than maximum shadow essence, the script will check the target for eligibility.
	If you have maximum shadow essence, it will cast the spell you set as your script variable.
	Mana upkeep via "sacrifice mana" is handled separately by the companion background
	script sacrifice_mana.lic -- run that alongside this one during a hunt.

	Can be run two ways:
	  - From Bigshot, passing an explicit target and spell: ;fizzsac <#targetid> 719
	  - Manually during a hunt, passing just the spell id: ;fizzsac 719
	    Target resolution order: an explicit #id you passed, then your formal
	    /target lock (GameObj.target) if you have one, then the first living
	    NPC in the room. If none of those find anything, the room is
	    considered empty and the script does nothing. Your own minor demon
	    (matched via IGNORE_NPCS, currently "verlok") is never picked as a
	    fallback target -- update that regex if you resummon a different
	    demon type.

	Set DEBUG = true/false at the top of the script to toggle the extra
	status messages (room-empty, appraisal) it prints along the way.

	incant() casts via Spell#force_incant instead of raw "release"/"incant"
	fput commands. Lich's Spell#cast internally queues through a shared
	lock (@@cast_lock) so only one script releases/prepares/casts a spell
	at a time across the whole session -- the same mechanism Bigshot's own
	spell commands (e.g. tether) use. Sending raw release/incant fput
	directly bypasses that queue entirely and can cancel whatever Bigshot
	is mid-cast on, which is what was causing Bigshot to keep recasting
	Tenebrous Tether (706) over and over during a hunt.

	A single invocation now loops the essence-check -> appraise/incant cycle
	on its own (up to MAX_ATTEMPTS times), instead of doing one step and
	exiting. Previously it took ~3 separate manual invocations to walk a
	target from full health down through the appraisal states to an actual
	sacrifice; now one ;fizzsac call keeps going until the target is
	dead/gone or MAX_ATTEMPTS is hit.

	Example bigshot line: script fizzsac target 719
		- Already have 5 shadow essence - casts 719 at target.
		- Under 5 shadow essence and target at full health - Casts 711.
		- Under 5 shadow essence and target appraises as "susceptible to manipulation" - Casts 706 for sacrifice bonus, then performs sacrifice.
		- Under 5 shadow essence and target appraises as "enticingly frail" - sacrifices target.
=end

DEBUG = true

IGNORE_NPCS = /verlok/i   # your own minor demon -- never a valid target

def debug(msg)
	echo "[DBG] #{msg}" if DEBUG
end

args = script.vars[1..-1].to_a.compact.map(&:to_s).reject(&:empty?)

explicit_target = args.find { |a| a.start_with?("#") }
spell_id = args.find { |a| a =~ /^\d+$/ }

if explicit_target
	target = explicit_target
elsif GameObj.target and GameObj.target.name !~ IGNORE_NPCS
	target = "##{GameObj.target.id}"
else
	# No formal /target lock -- fall back to the first living NPC in the room,
	# since most hunting doesn't use an explicit lock at all.
	npc = GameObj.npcs.find { |n| n.status !~ /dead|gone/i and n.name !~ IGNORE_NPCS }
	target = npc ? "##{npc.id}" : nil
end

unless spell_id
	echo "Usage: ;fizzsac <spell_id>  (uses your currently selected target)"
	echo "       ;fizzsac <#targetid> <spell_id>  (explicit target, e.g. from Bigshot)"
	exit
end

def sacrifice(target)
	waitrt?
	waitcastrt?
	fput "sacrifice #{target}"
	sleep 0.1
	waitrt?
end

def tether(target)
	waitrt?
	waitcastrt?
	Spell[706].cast("#{target}")
	sacrifice(target)
end

def pain(target)
	waitrt?
	waitcastrt?
	Spell[711].cast("#{target}")
end

def incant(spell_id)
	spell = Spell[spell_id]

	unless spell.affordable?
		debug("Skipping incant #{spell_id} -- not affordable (mana/spirit/stamina).")
		return
	end

	waitrt?
	waitcastrt?
	result = spell.force_incant
	debug("Incant #{spell_id} result: #{result}")
	result
end

def appraise(target)

	status = Lich::Util.issue_command("appraise #{target}", /^The .+? is \w+ in size/, include_end: false, quiet: true, silent: true).last

	debug("Appraise #{target}: #{status}")

	case status
	when /enticingly frail/
		sacrifice(target)
	when /susceptible to manipulation/
		tether(target)
	when /soul is stalwart and formidable|firmly bound|indomitable/
		pain(target)
	end
	
end

MAX_ATTEMPTS = 10

############################################
# Main
############################################

if target.nil?
	debug("Not doing anything because room is empty")
else
	echo "Finding: #{target}"

	search = target.delete_prefix("#")

	MAX_ATTEMPTS.times do |attempt|
		find = GameObj.npcs.find { |n| n.id == search }
		break if find.nil? or find.status =~ /dead|gone/

		shadow_essence = Resources.shadow_essence
		debug("Attempt #{attempt + 1}/#{MAX_ATTEMPTS}: ##{find.id}, shadow essence #{shadow_essence.to_i}/5")

		if shadow_essence.to_i < 5
			appraise("##{find.id}")
		else
			incant(spell_id)
		end

		waitrt?
		waitcastrt?
		sleep 0.5
	end
end
